**Additional Protections**:
- **Structured logging**: JSON format enables automated scanning and alerting on sensitive data patterns
- **Log aggregator configuration**: Configure Elasticsearch/Datadog field-level masking as backup
- **Retention policies**: Different retention periods for different log types (audit logs kept longer)
- **Access controls**: Implement RBAC on log aggregation systems with audit trails
- **Encryption**: Enable encryption at rest and in transit for all log data
- **Alerting**: Set up alerts for any logs containing potential sensitive data patterns
- **Regular audits**: Periodic scanning of log storage for accidentally logged sensitive data

Logging authentication events is crucial for security monitoring, but you must be extremely careful not to log sensitive data like passwords, tokens, or personal information. This was the exact mistake that led to Twitter's 2018 incident where 330 million users' passwords were exposed in plaintext logs.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;
import org.springframework.security.crypto.bcrypt.BCryptPasswordEncoder;

@Service
public class AuthenticationService {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(AuthenticationService.class);
    private final BCryptPasswordEncoder passwordEncoder = new BCryptPasswordEncoder();
    private final UserRepository userRepository;

    public AuthenticationService(UserRepository userRepository) {
        this.userRepository = userRepository;
    }

    public AuthenticationResult authenticate(String username, String password, String ipAddress) {
        // VULNERABLE: Logging password in plaintext!
        logger.info("Login attempt - User: {} Password: {} IP: {}", username, password, ipAddress);

        User user = userRepository.findByUsername(username);

        if (user == null) {
            // VULNERABLE: Logging attempted password for non-existent user
            logger.warn("Failed login - User not found: {} attempted password: {}", username, password);
            return AuthenticationResult.failure("Invalid credentials");
        }

        if (passwordEncoder.matches(password, user.getPasswordHash())) {
            // VULNERABLE: Logging session token and user details
            String sessionToken = generateSessionToken();
            logger.info("Successful login - User: {} Email: {} SSN: {} Token: {}", 
                       username, user.getEmail(), user.getSsn(), sessionToken);
            return AuthenticationResult.success(sessionToken);
        }

        // VULNERABLE: Password logged on failure
        logger.warn("Failed login - Invalid password for user: {} attempted: {}", username, password);
        return AuthenticationResult.failure("Invalid credentials");
    }

    private String generateSessionToken() {
        return java.util.UUID.randomUUID().toString();
    }
}
```

**Attack Scenario**:
```text
1. Attacker gains access to log files via:
   - Log aggregation system (Splunk, ELK) compromise
   - Server breach with log file access
   - Insider threat with log viewer permissions
   - Cloud storage misconfiguration (S3 bucket with logs)

2. Logs contain:
   - Plaintext passwords for credential stuffing
   - Session tokens for session hijacking
   - PII (SSN, email) for identity theft
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Passwords in logs enable credential stuffing attacks across multiple services
- Session tokens in logs allow session hijacking without authentication
- PII exposure violates GDPR, CCPA, HIPAA with fines up to millions
- Log files often have weaker access controls than databases
- Logs are frequently shipped to third-party services (Datadog, Splunk)

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import org.slf4j.MDC;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;
import org.springframework.security.crypto.bcrypt.BCryptPasswordEncoder;

@Service
public class SecureAuthenticationService {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(SecureAuthenticationService.class);
    private static final Logger auditLogger = LoggerFactory.getLogger("SECURITY_AUDIT");
    private final BCryptPasswordEncoder passwordEncoder = new BCryptPasswordEncoder();
    private final UserRepository userRepository;

    public SecureAuthenticationService(UserRepository userRepository) {
        this.userRepository = userRepository;
    }

    public AuthenticationResult authenticate(String username, String password, String ipAddress) {
        // Set correlation ID for request tracing
        String correlationId = java.util.UUID.randomUUID().toString().substring(0, 8);
        MDC.put("correlationId", correlationId);
        MDC.put("clientIp", maskIpAddress(ipAddress));

        try {
            // SECURE: Log attempt without sensitive data
            auditLogger.info("AUTH_ATTEMPT user={} ip_masked={}", 
                           maskUsername(username), maskIpAddress(ipAddress));

            User user = userRepository.findByUsername(username);

            if (user == null) {
                // SECURE: No password, no indication if username exists
                auditLogger.warn("AUTH_FAILED reason=invalid_credentials ip_masked={}", 
                               maskIpAddress(ipAddress));
                return AuthenticationResult.failure("Invalid credentials");
            }

            if (passwordEncoder.matches(password, user.getPasswordHash())) {
                String sessionToken = generateSessionToken();
                // SECURE: Log success with user ID only, no token or PII
                auditLogger.info("AUTH_SUCCESS user_id={} ip_masked={}", 
                               user.getId(), maskIpAddress(ipAddress));
                return AuthenticationResult.success(sessionToken);
            }

            // SECURE: Generic failure message, no password logged
            auditLogger.warn("AUTH_FAILED user_id={} reason=invalid_password ip_masked={}", 
                           user.getId(), maskIpAddress(ipAddress));
            return AuthenticationResult.failure("Invalid credentials");

        } finally {
            MDC.clear();
        }
    }

    private String maskUsername(String username) {
        if (username == null || username.length() < 3) return "***";
        return username.substring(0, 2) + "***";
    }

    private String maskIpAddress(String ip) {
        if (ip == null) return "unknown";
        // Mask last octet for privacy while maintaining some forensic value
        String[] parts = ip.split("\\.");
        if (parts.length == 4) {
            return parts[0] + "." + parts[1] + "." + parts[2] + ".xxx";
        }
        return "masked";
    }

    private String generateSessionToken() {
        return java.util.UUID.randomUUID().toString();
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Never log passwords**: Not even hashed versions - they can still be cracked
- **Mask PII**: Partially redact usernames, IPs, and other identifiable data
- **Use structured logging**: Enables filtering sensitive fields at the log aggregator level
- **Separate audit logs**: Security events go to dedicated audit log with stricter access controls
- **Correlation IDs**: Enable request tracing without exposing sensitive data

Excellent question. In production APIs, request/response logging is essential for debugging but extremely dangerous if not handled properly. The 2023 CircleCI breach exposed customer secrets partly due to overly verbose logging. Here's a production-grade approach:

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```java
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;
import org.springframework.web.filter.OncePerRequestFilter;
import org.springframework.web.util.ContentCachingRequestWrapper;
import org.springframework.web.util.ContentCachingResponseWrapper;

import javax.servlet.FilterChain;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.util.*;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;

@Component
public class SecureRequestLoggingFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(SecureRequestLoggingFilter.class);
    private static final Logger auditLogger = LoggerFactory.getLogger("API_AUDIT");
    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();

    // Sensitive field patterns - case insensitive
    private static final Set<String> SENSITIVE_FIELDS = Set.of(
        "password", "passwd", "pwd", "secret", "token", "api_key", "apikey",
        "authorization", "auth", "credit_card", "creditcard", "card_number",
        "cvv", "ssn", "social_security", "pin", "private_key", "privatekey",
        "access_token", "refresh_token", "session_id", "sessionid"
    );

    // Headers to never log
    private static final Set<String> SENSITIVE_HEADERS = Set.of(
        "authorization", "x-api-key", "cookie", "set-cookie", "x-auth-token"
    );

    // Patterns for detecting sensitive data in values
    private static final List<Pattern> SENSITIVE_PATTERNS = List.of(
        Pattern.compile("\\b\\d{3}-\\d{2}-\\d{4}\\b"),           // SSN
        Pattern.compile("\\b\\d{13,16}\\b"),                     // Credit card
        Pattern.compile("Bearer\\s+[A-Za-z0-9\\-._~+/]+"),       // Bearer token
        Pattern.compile("\\b[A-Za-z0-9]{32,}\\b")                // API keys
    );

    @Override
    protected void doFilterInternal(HttpServletRequest request, 
                                   HttpServletResponse response, 
                                   FilterChain filterChain) throws IOException {

        ContentCachingRequestWrapper wrappedRequest = new ContentCachingRequestWrapper(request);
        ContentCachingResponseWrapper wrappedResponse = new ContentCachingResponseWrapper(response);

        long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();
        String correlationId = UUID.randomUUID().toString().substring(0, 8);

        try {
            filterChain.doFilter(wrappedRequest, wrappedResponse);
        } finally {
            long duration = System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime;

            // Log sanitized request/response
            logRequest(wrappedRequest, correlationId);
            logResponse(wrappedResponse, correlationId, duration);

            // Copy response body back to original response
            wrappedResponse.copyBodyToResponse();
        }
    }

    private void logRequest(ContentCachingRequestWrapper request, String correlationId) {
        try {
            Map<String, Object> logEntry = new LinkedHashMap<>();
            logEntry.put("correlation_id", correlationId);
            logEntry.put("type", "REQUEST");
            logEntry.put("method", request.getMethod());
            logEntry.put("uri", sanitizeUri(request.getRequestURI()));
            logEntry.put("query_params", sanitizeQueryParams(request.getParameterMap()));
            logEntry.put("headers", sanitizeHeaders(request));
            logEntry.put("client_ip", maskIpAddress(request.getRemoteAddr()));

            // Only log body for non-GET requests
            if (!"GET".equals(request.getMethod())) {
                String body = new String(request.getContentAsByteArray());
                logEntry.put("body", sanitizeBody(body));
            }

            auditLogger.info(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(logEntry));

        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("Failed to log request: {}", e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    private void logResponse(ContentCachingResponseWrapper response, 
                            String correlationId, long durationMs) {
        try {
            Map<String, Object> logEntry = new LinkedHashMap<>();
            logEntry.put("correlation_id", correlationId);
            logEntry.put("type", "RESPONSE");
            logEntry.put("status", response.getStatus());
            logEntry.put("duration_ms", durationMs);

            // Only log response body for errors (debugging)
            if (response.getStatus() >= 400) {
                String body = new String(response.getContentAsByteArray());
                logEntry.put("body", sanitizeBody(body));
            }

            auditLogger.info(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(logEntry));

        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("Failed to log response: {}", e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    private String sanitizeBody(String body) {
        if (body == null || body.isEmpty()) return "[empty]";

        try {
            JsonNode node = objectMapper.readTree(body);
            if (node.isObject()) {
                return objectMapper.writeValueAsString(sanitizeJsonNode((ObjectNode) node));
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            // Not JSON, apply pattern-based sanitization
        }

        return sanitizeByPattern(body);
    }

    private ObjectNode sanitizeJsonNode(ObjectNode node) {
        ObjectNode sanitized = node.deepCopy();
        Iterator<String> fieldNames = sanitized.fieldNames();

        while (fieldNames.hasNext()) {
            String fieldName = fieldNames.next();

            if (isSensitiveField(fieldName)) {
                sanitized.put(fieldName, "[REDACTED]");
            } else if (sanitized.get(fieldName).isObject()) {
                sanitized.set(fieldName, sanitizeJsonNode((ObjectNode) sanitized.get(fieldName)));
            } else if (sanitized.get(fieldName).isTextual()) {
                String value = sanitized.get(fieldName).asText();
                sanitized.put(fieldName, sanitizeByPattern(value));
            }
        }

        return sanitized;
    }

    private boolean isSensitiveField(String fieldName) {
        return SENSITIVE_FIELDS.stream()
            .anyMatch(sensitive -> fieldName.toLowerCase().contains(sensitive));
    }

    private String sanitizeByPattern(String value) {
        String result = value;
        for (Pattern pattern : SENSITIVE_PATTERNS) {
            result = pattern.matcher(result).replaceAll("[REDACTED]");
        }
        return result;
    }

    private Map<String, String> sanitizeHeaders(HttpServletRequest request) {
        Map<String, String> headers = new LinkedHashMap<>();
        Enumeration<String> headerNames = request.getHeaderNames();

        while (headerNames.hasMoreElements()) {
            String name = headerNames.nextElement();
            if (SENSITIVE_HEADERS.contains(name.toLowerCase())) {
                headers.put(name, "[REDACTED]");
            } else {
                headers.put(name, request.getHeader(name));
            }
        }

        return headers;
    }

    private Map<String, String> sanitizeQueryParams(Map<String, String[]> params) {
        Map<String, String> sanitized = new LinkedHashMap<>();

        for (Map.Entry<String, String[]> entry : params.entrySet()) {
            if (isSensitiveField(entry.getKey())) {
                sanitized.put(entry.getKey(), "[REDACTED]");
            } else {
                sanitized.put(entry.getKey(), String.join(",", entry.getValue()));
            }
        }

        return sanitized;
    }

    private String sanitizeUri(String uri) {
        // Redact path parameters that might be sensitive
        // e.g., /users/john.doe@email.com -> /users/[REDACTED]
        return uri.replaceAll("/users/[^/]+", "/users/[ID]");
    }

    private String maskIpAddress(String ip) {
        if (ip == null) return "unknown";
        String[] parts = ip.split("\\.");
        if (parts.length == 4) {
            return parts[0] + "." + parts[1] + ".xxx.xxx";
        }
        return "masked";
    }
}
```

**Centralized Log Sanitization Configuration**:

```java
import ch.qos.logback.classic.spi.ILoggingEvent;
import ch.qos.logback.core.filter.Filter;
import ch.qos.logback.core.spi.FilterReply;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

public class SensitiveDataFilter extends Filter<ILoggingEvent> {

    private static final Pattern[] PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("(?i)(password|passwd|pwd)\\s*[=:]\\s*[^\\s,}]+"),
        Pattern.compile("(?i)(token|api_key|apikey)\\s*[=:]\\s*[^\\s,}]+"),
        Pattern.compile("\\b\\d{3}-\\d{2}-\\d{4}\\b"),
        Pattern.compile("\\b\\d{13,16}\\b"),
        Pattern.compile("Bearer\\s+[A-Za-z0-9\\-._~+/]+=")
    };

    @Override
    public FilterReply decide(ILoggingEvent event) {
        String message = event.getFormattedMessage();

        for (Pattern pattern : PATTERNS) {
            if (pattern.matcher(message).find()) {
                // Log warning about potential sensitive data leak
                // In production: alert security team
                return FilterReply.DENY;
            }
        }

        return FilterReply.NEUTRAL;
    }
}
```

