**Attack Scenario**:
```text
1. Attacker gains access to log files via:
   - Log aggregation service (Splunk, ELK) misconfiguration
   - Backup files exposure
   - Log shipping to insecure S3 bucket
   - Insider threat with log access

2. Extract credentials from logs:
   grep -r "Password:" /var/log/app/*.log

3. Result: Mass credential compromise affecting all logged users
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Passwords stored in plaintext violate PCI-DSS, GDPR, HIPAA
- Log files often have weaker access controls than databases
- Log aggregation systems may be accessible to many employees
- Logs are often backed up and retained for years
- Session tokens in logs enable session hijacking

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import org.slf4j.MDC;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;
import java.security.MessageDigest;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;

@Controller
public class SecureAuthenticationController {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(SecureAuthenticationController.class);
    private static final Logger auditLogger = LoggerFactory.getLogger("AUDIT");

    // Patterns for detecting sensitive data
    private static final Pattern SENSITIVE_PATTERNS = Pattern.compile(
        "(password|passwd|pwd|secret|token|apikey|api_key|authorization|bearer)",
        Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE
    );

    @PostMapping("/api/login")
    public String login(@RequestBody LoginRequest request, HttpServletRequest httpRequest) {

        // Generate correlation ID for request tracing
        String correlationId = generateCorrelationId();
        MDC.put("correlationId", correlationId);
        MDC.put("clientIp", maskIpAddress(httpRequest.getRemoteAddr()));

        try {
            // SECURE: Log only non-sensitive authentication events
            logger.info("Login attempt initiated for user: {}", 
                maskUsername(request.getUsername()));

            // SECURE: Never log passwords - log only that authentication was attempted
            User user = authenticateUser(request.getUsername(), request.getPassword());

            String sessionToken = generateSessionToken(user);

            // SECURE: Log only token hash for debugging, never the actual token
            logger.debug("Session created - tokenHash: {}", 
                hashForLogging(sessionToken));

            // SECURE: Structured audit log without sensitive data
            auditLogger.info("AUTH_SUCCESS userId={} method=password ipHash={}",
                user.getId(),
                hashForLogging(httpRequest.getRemoteAddr()));

            return "redirect:/dashboard";

        } catch (AuthenticationException e) {
            // SECURE: Log failure without credentials
            logger.warn("Authentication failed for user: {} - reason: {}",
                maskUsername(request.getUsername()),
                e.getMessage());  // Only message, not full stack with params

            auditLogger.warn("AUTH_FAILURE user={} reason={} ipHash={}",
                maskUsername(request.getUsername()),
                sanitizeErrorMessage(e.getMessage()),
                hashForLogging(httpRequest.getRemoteAddr()));

            return "redirect:/login?error";
        } finally {
            MDC.clear();
        }
    }

    // Mask username to show only first 2 characters
    private String maskUsername(String username) {
        if (username == null || username.length() < 3) {
            return "***";
        }
        return username.substring(0, 2) + "***";
    }

    // Create a one-way hash for logging (non-reversible)
    private String hashForLogging(String sensitiveValue) {
        try {
            MessageDigest md = MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA-256");
            byte[] hash = md.digest(sensitiveValue.getBytes());
            return bytesToHex(hash).substring(0, 8);  // First 8 chars only
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return "HASH_ERROR";
        }
    }

    private String maskIpAddress(String ip) {
        // Mask last octet for privacy
        if (ip != null && ip.matches("\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+")) {
            return ip.replaceAll("\\.\\d+$", ".xxx");
        }
        return "masked";
    }

    private String sanitizeErrorMessage(String message) {
        if (message == null) return "unknown";
        // Remove any accidentally included sensitive data
        return SENSITIVE_PATTERNS.matcher(message).replaceAll("[REDACTED]");
    }

    private String bytesToHex(byte[] bytes) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (byte b : bytes) {
            sb.append(String.format("%02x", b));
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }

    private String generateCorrelationId() {
        return java.util.UUID.randomUUID().toString().substring(0, 8);
    }

    private User authenticateUser(String username, String password) throws AuthenticationException {
        return null;
    }

    private String generateSessionToken(User user) {
        return java.util.UUID.randomUUID().toString();
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Never log credentials**: Passwords, tokens, API keys must never appear in logs
- **Mask PII**: Usernames, emails, IPs partially redacted
- **Hash for correlation**: Use one-way hashes when you need to correlate events
- **Separate audit logs**: Security events go to dedicated audit log with stricter controls
- **Sanitize error messages**: Remove accidentally included sensitive data from exceptions

A comprehensive logging sanitization framework requires multiple layers including custom log encoders, annotation-based field marking, and log injection prevention. This is essential for compliance with PCI-DSS Requirement 3.4 and GDPR Article 32.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```java
import ch.qos.logback.classic.encoder.PatternLayoutEncoder;
import ch.qos.logback.classic.spi.ILoggingEvent;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonIgnore;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonGenerator;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializerProvider;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.module.SimpleModule;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ser.std.StdSerializer;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;

import java.io.IOException;
import java.lang.annotation.*;
import java.lang.reflect.Field;
import java.util.*;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;

// Custom annotation to mark sensitive fields
@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)
@Target({ElementType.FIELD, ElementType.METHOD})
public @interface SensitiveData {
    MaskingStrategy strategy() default MaskingStrategy.FULL;
    String replacement() default "[REDACTED]";
}

public enum MaskingStrategy {
    FULL,           // Complete replacement
    PARTIAL,        // Show first/last chars
    HASH,           // SHA-256 hash (first 8 chars)
    EMAIL,          // user@*** format
    CARD,           // ****-****-****-1234
    PHONE           // ***-***-1234
}

// Secure logging wrapper
public class SecureLogger {

    private static final Logger internalLogger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(SecureLogger.class);
    private static final ObjectMapper sanitizingMapper;
    private static final Set<String> SENSITIVE_FIELD_NAMES;
    private static final Pattern LOG_INJECTION_PATTERN;
    private static final Pattern SENSITIVE_VALUE_PATTERN;

    static {
        // Initialize sensitive field detection
        SENSITIVE_FIELD_NAMES = new HashSet<>(Arrays.asList(
            "password", "passwd", "pwd", "secret", "token", "apikey", 
            "api_key", "apiKey", "authorization", "bearer", "credential",
            "ssn", "socialSecurityNumber", "creditCard", "cardNumber",
            "cvv", "pin", "accountNumber", "routingNumber", "privateKey",
            "secretKey", "accessToken", "refreshToken", "sessionId"
        ));

        // Pattern to detect log injection attempts
        LOG_INJECTION_PATTERN = Pattern.compile(
            "[\\r\\n]|%0[aAdD]|\\\\[rn]", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE
        );

        // Pattern to detect sensitive data in values
        SENSITIVE_VALUE_PATTERN = Pattern.compile(
            "(?i)(password|secret|token|key)\\s*[=:]\\s*\\S+"
        );

        // Configure sanitizing JSON mapper
        sanitizingMapper = new ObjectMapper();
        SimpleModule module = new SimpleModule();
        module.addSerializer(Object.class, new SanitizingSerializer());
        sanitizingMapper.registerModule(module);
    }

    private final Logger logger;
    private final String className;

    private SecureLogger(Class<?> clazz) {
        this.logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(clazz);
        this.className = clazz.getSimpleName();
    }

    public static SecureLogger getLogger(Class<?> clazz) {
        return new SecureLogger(clazz);
    }

    // Secure info logging with automatic sanitization
    public void info(String message, Object... args) {
        if (logger.isInfoEnabled()) {
            logger.info(sanitizeMessage(message), sanitizeArgs(args));
        }
    }

    public void warn(String message, Object... args) {
        if (logger.isWarnEnabled()) {
            logger.warn(sanitizeMessage(message), sanitizeArgs(args));
        }
    }

    public void error(String message, Object... args) {
        if (logger.isErrorEnabled()) {
            logger.error(sanitizeMessage(message), sanitizeArgs(args));
        }
    }

    public void debug(String message, Object... args) {
        if (logger.isDebugEnabled()) {
            logger.debug(sanitizeMessage(message), sanitizeArgs(args));
        }
    }

    // Audit logging with structured format
    public void audit(String eventType, Map<String, Object> details) {
        Map<String, Object> auditEvent = new LinkedHashMap<>();
        auditEvent.put("timestamp", System.currentTimeMillis());
        auditEvent.put("eventType", eventType);
        auditEvent.put("source", className);
        auditEvent.put("details", sanitizeMap(details));

        try {
            String jsonEvent = sanitizingMapper.writeValueAsString(auditEvent);
            logger.info("AUDIT: {}", jsonEvent);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("Failed to serialize audit event", e);
        }
    }

    // Prevent log injection attacks
    private String sanitizeMessage(String message) {
        if (message == null) return "";

        // Remove newlines and carriage returns (log injection)
        String sanitized = LOG_INJECTION_PATTERN.matcher(message).replaceAll("_");

        // Detect and mask sensitive patterns in message
        sanitized = SENSITIVE_VALUE_PATTERN.matcher(sanitized).replaceAll("[REDACTED]");

        // Limit message length to prevent log flooding
        if (sanitized.length() > 10000) {
            sanitized = sanitized.substring(0, 10000) + "...[TRUNCATED]";
        }

        return sanitized;
    }

    private Object[] sanitizeArgs(Object[] args) {
        if (args == null) return new Object[0];

        Object[] sanitized = new Object[args.length];
        for (int i = 0; i < args.length; i++) {
            sanitized[i] = sanitizeValue(args[i]);
        }
        return sanitized;
    }

    private Object sanitizeValue(Object value) {
        if (value == null) return null;

        if (value instanceof String) {
            return sanitizeMessage((String) value);
        }

        if (value instanceof Throwable) {
            return sanitizeException((Throwable) value);
        }

        if (value instanceof Map) {
            return sanitizeMap((Map<?, ?>) value);
        }

        if (value instanceof Collection) {
            return sanitizeCollection((Collection<?>) value);
        }

        // For complex objects, use reflection-based sanitization
        return sanitizeObject(value);
    }

    private Map<String, Object> sanitizeMap(Map<?, ?> map) {
        Map<String, Object> sanitized = new LinkedHashMap<>();
        for (Map.Entry<?, ?> entry : map.entrySet()) {
            String key = String.valueOf(entry.getKey());
            Object value = entry.getValue();

            if (isSensitiveFieldName(key)) {
                sanitized.put(key, "[REDACTED]");
            } else {
                sanitized.put(key, sanitizeValue(value));
            }
        }
        return sanitized;
    }

    private List<Object> sanitizeCollection(Collection<?> collection) {
        List<Object> sanitized = new ArrayList<>();
        int count = 0;
        for (Object item : collection) {
            if (count++ > 100) {
                sanitized.add("...[TRUNCATED: " + (collection.size() - 100) + " more items]");
                break;
            }
            sanitized.add(sanitizeValue(item));
        }
        return sanitized;
    }

    private String sanitizeObject(Object obj) {
        try {
            Map<String, Object> fieldMap = new LinkedHashMap<>();
            Class<?> clazz = obj.getClass();

            for (Field field : clazz.getDeclaredFields()) {
                field.setAccessible(true);
                String fieldName = field.getName();
                Object fieldValue = field.get(obj);

                // Check for @SensitiveData annotation
                SensitiveData annotation = field.getAnnotation(SensitiveData.class);
                if (annotation != null) {
                    fieldMap.put(fieldName, maskValue(fieldValue, annotation.strategy()));
                } else if (isSensitiveFieldName(fieldName)) {
                    fieldMap.put(fieldName, "[REDACTED]");
                } else if (field.getAnnotation(JsonIgnore.class) != null) {
                    // Skip JsonIgnore fields
                    continue;
                } else {
                    fieldMap.put(fieldName, sanitizeValue(fieldValue));
                }
            }

            return fieldMap.toString();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return "[SERIALIZATION_ERROR]";
        }
    }

    private String sanitizeException(Throwable throwable) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        sb.append(throwable.getClass().getSimpleName());
        sb.append(": ");
        sb.append(sanitizeMessage(throwable.getMessage()));

        // Limit stack trace depth
        StackTraceElement[] stackTrace = throwable.getStackTrace();
        int depth = Math.min(stackTrace.length, 10);
        for (int i = 0; i < depth; i++) {
            sb.append("\n\tat ").append(stackTrace[i].toString());
        }
        if (stackTrace.length > 10) {
            sb.append("\n\t... ").append(stackTrace.length - 10).append(" more");
        }

        return sb.toString();
    }

    private boolean isSensitiveFieldName(String fieldName) {
        if (fieldName == null) return false;
        String lower = fieldName.toLowerCase();
        return SENSITIVE_FIELD_NAMES.stream()
            .anyMatch(sensitive -> lower.contains(sensitive.toLowerCase()));
    }

    private String maskValue(Object value, MaskingStrategy strategy) {
        if (value == null) return null;
        String strValue = String.valueOf(value);

        switch (strategy) {
            case FULL:
                return "[REDACTED]";

            case PARTIAL:
                if (strValue.length() <= 4) return "****";
                return strValue.substring(0, 2) + "****" + 
                       strValue.substring(strValue.length() - 2);

            case HASH:
                return hashValue(strValue);

            case EMAIL:
                int atIndex = strValue.indexOf('@');
                if (atIndex > 0) {
                    return strValue.substring(0, Math.min(2, atIndex)) + "***@***";
                }
                return "***@***";

            case CARD:
                if (strValue.length() >= 4) {
                    return "****-****-****-" + strValue.substring(strValue.length() - 4);
                }
                return "****-****-****-****";

            case PHONE:
                if (strValue.length() >= 4) {
                    return "***-***-" + strValue.substring(strValue.length() - 4);
                }
                return "***-***-****";

            default:
                return "[REDACTED]";
        }
    }

    private String hashValue(String value) {
        try {
            java.security.MessageDigest md = java.security.MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA-256");
            byte[] hash = md.digest(value.getBytes(java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets.UTF_8));
            StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
                sb.append(String.format("%02x", hash[i]));
            }
            return "hash:" + sb.toString();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return "[HASH_ERROR]";
        }
    }
}

